In Hibernate 6 it&#39;s no longer possible to reuse `Predicate`s across different `CriteriaQueries`. In your case it&#39;s straightforward to fix with a simple refactor to create a new `Predicate` for the count query:

```
private long getEmployeesCount(EmployeeSearchCriteria searchCriteria) {
  CriteriaQuery&lt;Long&gt; countQuery = criteriaBuilder.createQuery(Long.class);
  Root&lt;Employee&gt; countRoot = countQuery.from(Employee.class);
  Predicate predicate = getPredicate(searchCriteria, countRoot);
  countQuery.select(criteriaBuilder.count(countRoot)).where(predicate);
  return entityManager.createQuery(countQuery).getSingleResult();
}
